INDEED the Thing is too great to be amplified on or magnified by any Words of Man! It was a kind of Day of Judgment, and they that felt the Terror of it prayed they might never again see or hear the like. The Scripture abounds in the rhetorical and lofty De∣scriptions

of it;
Psal. lxviii. 8. xcvii. 5. GOD came from Sinai, the HOLY ONE from Mount Seir, with ten thousand of his Saints; they sat down at his Feet, to receive his Words: The Earth shook, even Sinai it self at the Presence of the LORD: His Thunder was in the Heavens, his Lightnings light'ned the World, the Earth trembled and shook, and all the People saw his Glory, worship Him all ye Gods.
